od.',5,'[213.6, 24.0, 0.0, 26.0, 31.0, 16.0, 0.0]'),(43026,'chile rellenos',45,52268,'2002-10-14','a favorite from a local restaurant no longer in business. not an authentic mexican chile relleno, but a crispy, flaky version.',9,'[94.0, 10.0, 0.0, 11.0, 11.0, 21.0, 0.0]'),(43164,'mr  grant you took half veal prince orloff',120,28201,'2002-10-14','i couldn\'t resist! named in honor of one of my all time favorite ',26,'[510.6, 50.0, 10.0, 21.0, 90.0, 70.0, 1.0]'),(44045,'mennonite  corn fritters',15,41706,'2002-10-25','ok - my heritage has been revealed. :) these are simply wonderful. a favorite among our community, they\'re sure to bring a smile to your face. enjoy!',6,'[67.1, 7.0, 2.0, 7.0, 3.0, 10.0, 1.0]'),(44061,'amish  tomato ketchup  for canning',190,41706,'2002-10-25','my dh\'s amish mother raised him on this recipe. he much prefers it over store-bought ketchup. it was a taste i had to acquire, but now my ds\'s also prefer this type of ketchup. enjoy!',5,'[352.9, 1.0, 337.0, 23.0, 3.0, 0.0, 28.0]'),(44123,'george s at the cove  black bean soup',90,35193,'2002-10-25','an original recipe created by chef scott meskan, george\'s at the cove. we enjoyed this when we visited this restaurant in la jolla, california. this recipe is requested so often, they have it printed and ready at the hostess stand. it\'s unbeatable at the restaurant, but i do a pretty good job at home, too, if i do say so myself!',11,'[804.7, 108.0, 26.0, 19.0, 28.0, 214.0, 10.0]'),(44895,'symphony  brownies',45,51224,'2002-10-29','a ',10,'[5728.3, 470.0, 1941.0, 87.0, 140.0, 443.0, 226.0]'),(45859,'truth serum  margaritas',30,59756,'2002-11-13','you\'ll know why i call it truth serum after you\'ve finished one of these ! be careful, they are strong. i avoid margarita mixes, because they seem to taste so artificial--there is no substitute for fresh lime juice. when limes are on sale, i buy lots and juice them all. i freeze the juice in 12 oz water bottles, so it\'s ready to go for ',3,'[72.0, 0.0, 61.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 6.0]'),(47366,'forgotten  minestrone',495,31871,'2002-11-21','this recipe came from a ',5,'[346.9, 24.0, 18.0, 42.0, 42.0, 30.0, 10.0]'),(48156,'emotional balance  spice mixture',10,6164,'2002-12-09','really an effective spice blend...i got it in one of maharishi ayurveda newsletters and thought of sharing here !hope this will help you melt your blues away.. :-))',2,'[182.7, 11.0, 4.0, 1.0, 13.0, 4.0, 10.0]'),(49262,'easiest ever  hollandaise sauce',25,64428,'2002-12-19','the secret to this easy hollandaise sauce is in separating the egg yolks. remove all the egg whites, as they can thin the sauce. also, it is best prepared in a double boiler to prevent overheating. serve over cooked asparagus, broccoli, or broiled tomatoes.',7,'[1290.4, 213.0, 4.0, 53.0, 22.0, 417.0, 1.0]'),(50184,'cream  of mushroom soup',40,20477,'2003-01-07','when i was vegan, i missed good cream soups. this one has an excellent, unique flavor. it isn\'t low fat though, sorry.',8,'[473.2, 59.0, 23.0, 7.0, 28.0, 36.0, 8.0]'),(50662,'25 000 casserole',125,9748,'2003-01-10','this is a recipe that my mother got from some cooking contest in the \'50s. it is delicious and filling on a cold night. we all loved it so much that we would call it the 25 billion dollar casserole! unfortunately, my family isn\'t big on dumplings, so i can\'t make this as often as i would like.',15,'[2450.5, 325.0, 20.0, 90.0, 75.0, 435.0, 32.0]'),(52443,'pizza  stuffed potato',25,1533,'2003-01-28','',8,'[183.3, 12.0, 9.0, 15.0, 21.0, 23.0, 6.0]'),(52804,'jiffy  extra moist carrot cake',50,49304,'2003-01-29','this is a very tasty, moist, carrot cake. a nice sized cake for 2 or 3 people.',8,'[612.1, 49.0, 170.0, 25.0, 15.0, 39.0, 25.0]'),(53402,'killer  lasagna',90,60512,'2003-02-04','this was originally my mom\'s recipe and used to be a favorite when we were kids. i always requested it for my birthday dinner.',13,'[370.5, 38.0, 21.0, 57.0, 53.0, 64.0, 3.0]'),(53872,'cheeseburger  meatloaf for lactose in